race.comment: MR MARRAKECH (1) delivered a hat-trick and then showed good early dash last start and held on well to finish a head back in third over 1200m at this track. In the top barn and is nicely placed to go a couple better. Stablemate PRINCE RUBAN (4) is back in Darwin after a first-up run at Mornington where he dropped away from the pace at long odds. He flies this track/trip and has been freshened 29 days. Todd rides and the betting will be key. JULY (5) switched from a Queensland yard and was placed here in a CL2. That stacks up and he tumbles in weight. Fitter and has to be considered. ORION THE HUNTER (2) has been freshened and went well enough here two back to consider.
